	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="After Ambush with Harper path:&#xD;&#xA;- Go to Region: Haven -&gt; Bridge&#xD;&#xA;- set Act 2 Thiefling Path&#xD;&#xA;- pass the entrance cinematic&#xD;&#xA;- Go to Region: Haven -&gt; Isobel Room&#xD;&#xA;- talk to Isobel -&gt; Initiate Attack by Marcus&#xD;&#xA;- talk to Harper at goto -48, 135&#xD;&#xA;- SetGlobalOsirisFlag SCL_Drider_State_HarpersWaitingAtBridge&#xD;&#xA;- talk to Harpers on the bridge&#xD;&#xA;- follow them to Ambush site goto 0, -27&#xD;&#xA;- debug: Kill Combat&#xD;&#xA;- Talk to Harper (Branthos)&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;After Ambush with Drider path:&#xD;&#xA;- go to Region: SCL -&gt; Mountain Pass&#xD;&#xA;- set Act 2 Absolute Path&#xD;&#xA;- goto 92.91, 51.44, -50.63&#xD;&#xA;- talk to Kansif, perform the Lyre&#xD;&#xA;- talk to Drider&#xD;&#xA;- follow the Drider to Ambush site goto 14, -18&#xD;&#xA;- enter Combat, but Kill Drider&#xD;&#xA;- talk to the Harper (take the lantern or let Harper take the lantern)." />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="1599" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="Harper leader after the fight with the Drider. You started the fight on drider's side, but switched and sided with the Harpers. They take the lantern and if you want it, you need to attack them or convince them to give it to you." />
